node.text:
"Understanding different asset classes can be key for long-term success

For beginners, @Robbywclark recommends matching your liability expenses with your asset purchases💰

Here's Robby's breakdown of different asset classes he likes for long-term success:

1. Real estate. Buy a property and rent it out. That’ll help pay down equity while also having a consistent cash flow🏡

2. Stocks are a traditional investment vehicle. Historically they tend to be a safe investment over the long run that will accumulate big returns over time.

3. I love cryptocurrencies, but to an old-school investor they would be considered risky, so limit your exposure when starting, but don’t miss out!

4. Whole/universal life insurance policies can also be a great investment vehicle and are utilized by savvy investors as well as ultra-high network individuals to invest in their future."

node.title: Robby’s Rantz Episode 7 - Investing as an Entertainer with @edwestwick

node.text:
This is truer than people realize...⁣
⁣
Everyone has a million and one excuses why they don't start a business, start investing, start writing, start a YouTube channel, etc etc.⁣
⁣
But most people do not acknowledge that embarrassment is one of their reasons for not starting.⁣
⁣
And it is embarrassing. For people you know to see your project before it is successful.⁣
⁣
However, it is essential you overcome this.⁣
⁣
And once you've overcome it once, you become fearless in future.⁣
⁣
Remember: society wants everyone to be the same, those who stick their neck out above the crowd will always be judged and shamed.⁣
⁣
But it's those people that stick their necks out, those who overcome the fear of starting from the bottom that go on to achieve great things and live incredible lives.⁣
⁣
P.s; I can't actually find a reliable source for this quote actually been said, despite seeing it quoted often, so keep that in mind. It's a good quote regardless which is why I'm sharing it.⁣
⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
The stock market is one of the best vehicles to grow your wealth out there...⁣
⁣
If you buy good companies and hold onto them for decades, your net worth will rocket. 🚀⁣
⁣
Of course, you can't get rich just from stocks (at least, not quick enough to enjoy the money pre 50s) but it is one of the best ways (if not the best) to take wealth you have built and let it grow for your passively.⁣
⁣
This is what I did:⁣
⁣
1) Saved as much money as possible by living frugally and doing odd jobs/side hustles.⁣
⁣
2) Invested it into a business.⁣
⁣
3) Once the business was successful, I invested a portion of the profits into my stock portfolio so my wealth could grow passively.⁣
⁣
This way I get the best of both worlds.⁣
⁣
My net worth grows passively, whilst I can accelerate the process of becoming wealthy by actively working on my business.⁣
⁣⁣⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Investing | Finance | Business on September 01, 2021 tagging @investearnsave. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '2 DAYS OF PROCRASTINATION CAN DESTROY 2 MONTHS OF DISCIPLINE. READ THAT AGAIN INVESTEARNSAVE'.

node.text:
This is definitely true to an extent, however let me add a VERY important caveat...⁣
⁣
People often decide not to start a good habit because they know at some point in the future they'll have to stop for an extended period of time.⁣
⁣
So they think: "Why start now?" I'll wait until I know I can do it without interruption.⁣
⁣
This is not a good mindset to have.⁣
⁣
Starting a habit for the first time is 100x harder than starting it again for a second time after time off.⁣
⁣
That's why NOW is always the best time to start a habit - get the difficult part away with.⁣
⁣
Then, if you have to have a few months off a good habit, it's much easier to get back into it afterwards and you haven't lost all the benefits of doing it the first time round.⁣
⁣
I noticed this after I had to take 6 weeks off working out. Although it was difficult to start again, I had way more strength than when I first started working out and my willpower was far higher. ⁣
⁣
So, whilst this post is often true. I'd always take 2 days off over not starting at all. ⁣
⁣
Get started on good habits!⁣
⁣
To quote Goggins, stay hard!⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣
⁣
#davidgoggins

"KNOW YOUR WORTH" INVESTEARNSAVE'.

node.text:
I know you see posts like this a lot, but stop for a second and imagine turning down $3 billion...⁣
⁣
I bet you've never saw a post like this and really thought about it.⁣
⁣
That must be incredibly difficult without the power of hindsight. I'd like to say I'd believe in my project and my ability to grow it so much I'd turn down $3 billion - in reality, I know I'd be very very very tempted to take it.⁣
⁣
Even after splitting it between various shareholders, as one of the founders you're sitting on enough money to last countless lifetimes - more money than you'd ever need.⁣
⁣
This shows the mindset of high performing entrepreneurs.⁣
⁣
If they can turn down such huge amounts of money, you can get an insight into just how confident they are, and how much they believe in their ability to succeed.⁣
⁣
Would you be able to turn down $3 billion? Let me know below.⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

node.text:
What's the lesson? Here it is:⁣
⁣
For good or for bad (I'll leave you all to debate it), we live in a world that requires specialists.⁣
⁣
There's just too many people in the world who are all interconnected for people who are just kind of good at a lot of things to get anywhere. ⁣
⁣
Because the market demands each role be filled by someone who is specialist at it.⁣
⁣
This means you can achieve a lot more in life if you become really, really good at a few things.⁣
⁣
Yes, you should devote some time to building up a broad range of skills and good habits, but you should also pick 1 or 2 things that will be YOUR things. Your areas of expertise, the things you can become one of the best in the world at.⁣
⁣
This kind of specialism makes you highly effective and valuable to the global marketplace. In return, it will help you amass great wealth.⁣
⁣
This is the lesson.⁣
⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Investing | Finance | Business on August 30, 2021 tagging @investearnsave. May be an image of text that says 'As soon as you realise the key to success is doing what others are not prepared to, you win at life. INVESTEARNSAVE'.

node.text:
It's simple, it's really simple and yet most people don't or pretend not to know it...⁣
⁣
There's no trick, no secret, no guru course or no mentor that can bypass this rule.⁣
⁣
You must be prepared to do the things other people are not if you wish to be successful.⁣
⁣
This can mean a lot of things, from personal experience here are some of the things:⁣
⁣
Taking 12 months away from socialising, only infrequently socialising whilst you build up a new business. ⁣
⁣
Selling your games consoles and cancelling your Netflix subscription. ⁣
⁣
Investing 100s of hours of time into a project you cannot be sure will succeed.⁣
⁣
Trying something new when you put that time into a project that fails, instead of giving up there.⁣
⁣
These are just a few examples. I'm sure you will come across different ones. The message is: do what others are not prepared to do and success will come to you.⁣
⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

DON'T GO BROKE TRYING To LOOK RICH. INVESTEARNSAVE'.

node.text:
Simple, but true...⁣
⁣
So many people are obsessed with looking wealthy, only few are obsessed with actually becoming wealthy.⁣
⁣
When I was in London recently I noticed even in the poorer parts, everyone had a shiny BMW, Audi, Mercedes, everyone was wearing designer clothes.⁣
⁣
In such a big city, a city full of prosperity, they felt like they had to play the status game to fit in. ⁣
⁣
It's all about appearances.⁣
⁣
Yet there's people out in the countryside who are millionaires with no fancy car and no designer clothes. They're far enough away from the status game that they don't feel the need to play it.⁣
⁣
They can afford the best holidays, the best food and have amazing homes. Because they built real wealth.⁣
⁣
I'm not saying you need to move out the city, just that you need to move out the status game.⁣
⁣
Don't try to become the richest looking person you know, try to become the actual richest person you know.⁣
⁣
Change the mentality. ⁣
⁣
Don’t miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣⁣

Reading WILL change your life, it's not just a cliche...⁣
⁣
Yes, you have to actually do things too. Reading isn't a substitute for action, or exploring the world first hand and building personal experience. However, it will level up your mind exponentially and inform what kind of action you take and help you skip some of the steps of experience building.⁣
⁣
If you're not reading, you're missing out.⁣
⁣
Find a book that interests you and start reading it.⁣
⁣
I'm at 33 books for the year, aiming to read 50 by the end and I've felt a noticeable difference in myself, my work and my debates with others. ⁣
⁣
